HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 67
By Stevens
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Eagleville High
School Eagles baseball team upon winning its
third consecutive TSSAA Class A state
championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
student athletes who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true
champions of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, again proving themselves to be the fiercest of competitors and, as such,
deserving of the highest regard, the Eagleville High School Eagles baseball team captured the
2024 TSSAA Class A state championship; and
WHEREAS, the Eagles won consecutive state titles in 2022 and 2023, and thus the
2024 championship completes the three-peat, a rare accomplishment; and
WHEREAS, after winning the District 9 regular-season crown and earning a number-one
seed in regional competition, Eagleville easily defeated Cornersville 9-3 and Richland 13-3 to
advance to the sectional round, in which the Eagles bested Collinwood 2-0 to secure a berth in
the state tournament; and
WHEREAS, arriving in Murfreesboro with an excellent 30-5 overall record, the Eagles
truly hit their stride, winning four consecutive games to be crowned state champions; and
WHEREAS, Eagleville walloped Union City 16-1, blasted Oakdale 17-2, and crushed
South Pittsburg 11-1 to reach the championship game of the state tourney unbeaten; and
WHEREAS, in the final tilt, the Eagles soared past University School of Johnson City,
blanking their rivals 10-0, to take home the state championship trophy; and
