WHEREAS, the Eagles were fortunate to enjoy the expertise and leadership of Coach
Brandon Bassham and his assistant coaches, Marty McCleary and Todd Williamson; managers
Trace McLeary and Hunter Sweeney also provided valuable assistance to the squad; and
WHEREAS, the following young men are proud to fly like an Eagle: Brayden Baker, Koltt
Bassham, Carter Blair, Maddox Bouldin, Nathan Brown, Alex Bryant, Krymson Burks, Brady
Burns, Sam Dodd, Donovan Drew, Jr Duke, Brycen Edging, Brody Gleason, Joshua Jeffcoat,
Karsyn Knowles, Cason G. Lamb, Tucker McLeary, Brody McLemore, Christopher Range,
Spencer Robbins, Drake Rzemieniewski, Adrian Sevieri, Micah Sevieri, Marshall Spann, Mason
Spears, Jacob Sweeney, and Elijah Watkins; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Eagleville High School baseball team epitomize all that
is good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in
competition while exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of these young men
not only made possible a championship season but also surely bode well for their success in
every future endeavor; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud the members of the Eagleville High School baseball team for their outstanding
performance and for serving as examples of the exceptional quality of the youth of Tennessee;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Eagleville High School Eagles baseball
team upon winning its third consecutive TSSAA Class A state championship in 2024 and extend
to each of these gifted athletes our best wishes for every continued success in all future
endeavors.
